This is contained in a four-year strategic plan, meant to upgrade the hospital into a Level Six facility, which was unveiled by Meru Governor Kiraitu Murungi on Tuesday.
Under the plan, the hospital will be transformed into a referral only facility, offering specialised services such as cancer treatment, intensive care services, dialysis and imaging among others.
Earlier, Governor Murungi said the county needs about Sh6 billion for infrastructure development for the hospital to attain the Level Six status.



