“This plan is part of the Meru Vision 2040 which envisions Meru County as a regional hub for medical care. We want to have high quality medical facilities offering specialised treatment for conditions that are currently treated abroad. I will soon be unveiling a new hospital board led by Prof Jotham Micheni to implement this plan,” Mr Murungi said.
Health budget
He said his administration is spending over 30 per cent of its budget on health, adding that the establishment of a renal unit, ICU and an oncology unit as well as the ongoing construction of a 300-bed ward will help in offering better services.
The governor said Level Four hospitals in Meru are also being upgraded to prepare for phasing out of walk-in patients at the referral facility.



